The documents provide information that supports this statement. Specifically, multiple documents mention that Podgorica has been the capital city of Montenegro since 1992 (after it was renamed from Titograd in 1992) and remains so even after Montenegro gained independence in 2006.

llama3.1.reason: The claim is wrong because Podgorica was actually the capital of Montenegro from April 2, 1992 to May 21, 2006.
